<tr><td valign=top colspan=5><table border=0 width="100%"><tr><td><font size="+1"><B><a name="529">Classic</a></B> / IPD No. <a class="linkid"  href="machine.cgi?id=529">529</a> <I>/ July, 1937 / 1 Player</I></font><br>&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=top></td></tr></table></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=top align=right><b>Average Fun Rating: </b></td><td colspan=4 width="80%" align=left valign=top><font color=red>No ratings on file</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[ <a href="rate/login.pl?gid=529" target="do_a_rating">Be first to rate this game!</a> ]
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Manufacturer: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games manufactured by 'Bally'"><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;mfgid=47">Bally Manufacturing Corporation (1931-1983) <i>[Trade Name: Bally</i>]</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Date Of Manufacture: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>July, 1937</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Model Number: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>160</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Type: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Electro-mechanical (EM)&nbsp;<a href="showhelp.pl?item=type&amp;highlight=EM#EM" title="Show Type Classifications" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align="right" valign=baseline><b>Serial Number Database:</b></td><td colspan=4 align="left" valign=baseline><a href="redirect.pl?http://www.ipsnd.net/View.aspx?id=529">View at <I>The Internet Pinball Serial Number Database</I> (IPSND.net)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1"><I>(External site)</i></font></td></tr><tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Theme: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Auto Racing - Horse Racing</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Specialty: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Payout Machine&nbsp;<a href="glossary.php#Payout_Machine" title="Explain this specialty" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a><br>
One Ball Game&nbsp;<a href="glossary.php#One_Ball_Game" title="Explain this specialty" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a><br>
Flipperless&nbsp;<a href="glossary.php#Flipperless" title="Explain this specialty" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notable Features: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>1 ball for 5 cents. Scoring <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Bumper">bumpers</a> (23). <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Spinning_Bumper">Spinning&nbsp;bumper</a> (advertised here as a 'whirling <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Bumper">bumper</a>', it is the bottom-most red-colored <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Bumper">bumper</a> on the playfield). Steel <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Playfield">playfield</a>. Projection score. Electronic tubes in main <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Cabinet">cabinet</a>. Game advertised as 54 inches long by 26 inches wide.</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notes: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>The patent for the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Spinning_Bumper">spinning&nbsp;bumper</a> on this game appears to be this one:<br><br>Patent No. 2,219,934 [BALL ROLLING GAME] filed August 24, 1937. Granted October 29, 1940 to Nels A. Nelson, assignor to Raymond T. Moloney.<br><br>The Billboard ad shows horses on the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Backglass">backglass</a>, while the flyer pictured here shows cars on the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Backglass">backglass</a>. One game of each version is pictured as well.<br><br>The flyer shown here advertises the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Cabinet">cabinet</a> as 46 inches wide, a misprint. The Billboard ad shows it as 26 inches.<br><br>Also available in a ticket model.<P></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align=right valign=baseline><b>Photos in: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>
The Billboard, Jul-10-1937, page 98<br>
<a href="redirect.pl?http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/9780764315275/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=9780764315275&linkCode=as2&tag=theinternetpi-20&linkId=Z72T2JLDLWNKE4TA">The Pinball Compendium 1930s - 1960s</a>, page 20<br>
</td></tr>
